1. Sliding Window (Most Important)

Use when:

Array contains positive numbers
Need longest/shortest/count subarray
Condition depends on current window

Examples:

Longest subarray with sum K (positive numbers)
Maximum sum subarray of size K
Fruits into baskets
Longest substring without repeating characters



2. Prefix Sum

Use when:

Sum queries
Sum K
Range sum



3. Prefix Sum + HashMap

This is probably the most important interview pattern.

Used for:

Subarray sum equals K
Longest subarray with sum K
Count subarrays with sum K
Binary array sum problems




4. Kadane's Algorithm

Use when:

Maximum subarray sum




5. Monotonic Stack

Use when:

Next greater element
Previous smaller element
Largest rectangle
Sum of subarray minimums

Examples:

Largest Rectangle in Histogram
Daily Temperatures
Sum of Subarray Minimums